## Should You Change the Stack?

**No. Here's the final take:**

| Question | Answer |
|---|---|
| Should I ditch React? | No. It's the right choice for a game with many dynamic views. |
| Should I use Next.js instead? | Not necessarily. Next.js adds SSR complexity you don't need — the game is behind login, so SEO isn't important. Stick with CRA/Vite (SPA). |
| Should I ditch Django for FastAPI? | No. Django's ORM, migrations, and built-in admin are very valuable here. FastAPI would make you rebuild a lot of that. |
| Should I ditch Node? | No. The Django→Node auth delegation pattern you've built is correct and clean. |
| Should I use GraphQL? | Not for now. REST is simpler and fine for this use case. |
| Should I use TypeScript? | For a learning project doubling as a portfolio, **yes — eventually**. It will dramatically catch bugs. Not urgent for now. |

